==Japanese==
===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab-top}}
! [[神]] || [[無]] || [[月]]
{{ja-kanjitab-bottom}}
[[神]] (かみ, ''kami''), "god" + [[無]] (な, ''na''), "lack" + [[月]] (つき, ''tsuki''), "month"
:Japanese gods were said to assemble at the [[w:Izumo Taisha|Grand shrine of ''Izumo'']] (出雲大社, ''Izumo Taisha'') in the tenth month of the lunar calendar, leaving no gods in the rest of Japan.

===Noun===
'''神無月''' ([[かみなづき]], ''kaminazuki'' or [[かんなづき]], ''kan'nazuki'')

# {{archaic}} the tenth month of the lunar calendar
# {{poetic}} the month of no gods; [[October]]

====Alternate forms====
* [[神有月]], [[神在月]]
*: Note: the above two forms are used only in [[w:Izumo Province|''Izumo'' Province]] ([[出雲国]]).

